      <section eId="sec_10_7_21">
        <num>10-7-21</num>
        <content>
          <p>Any change in the nature or terms of a contract is called a "novation"; such novation, without the consent of the surety, discharges him.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2130; Code 1868, § 2125; Code 1873, § 2153; Code 1882, § 2153; Civil Code 1895, § 2971; Civil Code 1910, § 3543; Code 1933, § 103-202.)</p>
